<component type="desktop">
  <id>io.github.tx00100xt.BerserkerQuake2</id>
  <name>BerserkerQuake2</name>
  <summary>BerserkerQuake2 is an graphically enhanced client for id Software's Quake II</summary>
  <metadata_license>CC0-1.0</metadata_license>
  <project_license>GPL-2.0</project_license>

  <developer_name>Andrei Drexler</developer_name>

  <url type="homepage">http://berserker.quakegate.ru/</url>
  <url type="bugtracker">https://github.com/tx00100xt/BerserkerQuake2/issues</url>
  <url type="help">https://github.com/tx00100xt/BerserkerQuake2/wiki</url>

  <launchable type="desktop-id">io.github.tx00100xt.BerserkerQuake2.desktop</launchable>

  <description>
    <p>BerserkerQuake2 engine that modernizes some elements of the Quake 2 graphical system.
       This Berserker engine supports real-time per-pixel lighting and shadow volumes, parallax,
       mirrors, fog, decal system, high resolution textures, and more..</p>
    <p>BerserkerQuake2 requires a copy of the Quake II game data (Steam, GOG or Quake original CD), and also 
       additionally freely distributed under the GPL-2.0 license extra game data for BerserkerQuake2. In order
       to set this up, open (and if necessary create) the directory <code>~/.berserkerq2</code> on your computer 
       and copy the <code>baseq2</code> directory from a copy of Quake original CD, and also extra game data there. 
       For more info visit: https://github.com/tx00100xt/BerserkerQuake2</p>
  </description>

